tests.sic.rnqt.nbin

Class RnQTCnbinOpt

  • java.lang.Object
    • tests.sic.rnqt.nbin.RnQTCnbinOpt
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OptimizerIntf

    public class RnQTCnbinOpt
extends java.lang.Object
implements OptimizerIntf
    class implements an optimizer over ALL three variables of the (R,nQ,T) policy, namely the reorder point R, the batch size Q and the review period T. The system being optimized faces stochastic demands as described in the class RnQTCnbin. The solution found is guaranteed to be the global optimum (subject to the step-size constraints for each of the decision variables). The optimizer is a parallel/distributed method, submitting tasks to optimize over the first two variables, for fixed review period T, where the review period T is increased from the Tmin value it can take on (user-defined) up to a point where the lower-bound on the cost function (namely the cost function with Ko=0) strictly exceeds the best known cost.

    Notes:

    • 20191115: program produces a visualization of the curve C*(T) for all T it tries. Also, the same RnQTCnbinOpt object can no longer simultaneously run many different optimization tasks (the method minimize() will wait until there are no threads running the same method of the same object before it starts running itself.) This is because we now need to keep track of the series of the T-values tried, and their corresponding costs so we can visualize them in the main program execution.
    • 2020-04-25: added method seParams() (public) because it was moved up from LocalOptimizerIntf to the root OptimizerIntf interface class.
